The Chronicle Mashudu Netsianda, Senior Reporter
ZIMBABWE Newspapers (Zimpapers) on Thursday unveiled a state-of-art printing press at its Bulawayo branch in Belmont industrial area as the integrated media continues to consolidate its market in the cut throat industry. The printing press, with has a capacity to print 40 000 newspaper copies for 12-page broadsheet sections or 24-page tabloid sections in full colour. <img class="alignnone wp-image-472114 size-large" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/10/new-press1-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/10/new-press1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/10/new-press1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Zimpapers chairman Dr Tommy Sithole officially opened the facility at the company’s Typocrafters building in Belmont. 